♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.886 --> 01:46.497
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

01:46.628 --> 01:48.978
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

01:54.505 --> 01:56.768
BAYWATCH

02:01.860 --> 02:03.993
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

02:04.124 --> 02:07.605
"FIRE WITH FIRE"

02:19.574 --> 02:23.099
[TECHNO MUSIC PLAYING]

04:26.178 --> 04:27.963
HEY, HOW YOU DOING?

04:30.008 --> 04:31.271
THAT'S GOOD.

04:35.797 --> 04:37.146
WHY IS IT THAT YOU ALWAYS
HAVE TO PICK

04:37.277 --> 04:38.843
THE MOST DANGEROUS SPORTS, HUH?

04:38.974 --> 04:41.542
FIRST IT WAS
THE RUBBER DUCKY RACING AND NOW,

04:42.499 --> 04:44.196
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT THAT THING IS CALLED.

04:44.327 --> 04:45.981
IT'S CALLED A STREET LUGE.

04:46.111 --> 04:48.375
IT'S THE MOST INCREDIBLE RUSH
I'VE EVER EXPERIENCED.

04:48.505 --> 04:50.246
YOU SHOULD TRY IT SOMETIME.

04:50.377 --> 04:51.769
NO, THANK YOU.

04:52.379 --> 04:54.381
IT'S NOT THAT DANGEROUS
ONCE YOU KNOW WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

04:55.120 --> 04:56.948
I COULD GIVE YOU LESSONS.

04:57.079 --> 04:58.646
REALLY?

04:58.863 --> 05:00.343
AND HOW DO YOU EXPECT TO DO THAT

05:00.474 --> 05:02.345
WHEN WE HARDLY SEE
EACH OTHER ANYMORE?

05:02.563 --> 05:04.304
THAT WILL SOON CHANGE, MY LOVE.

05:05.174 --> 05:06.349
NO, IT WON'T.

05:09.744 --> 05:11.180
IT'S NOT GONNA CHANGE AS LONG

05:11.311 --> 05:12.834
AS YOU'RE STILL MARRIED
TO KATHLEEN.

05:13.922 --> 05:17.926
I TOLD YOU, IMMIGRATION SERVICES
HELD UP MY GREEN CARD,

05:18.492 --> 05:20.320
ONCE IT COMES THROUGH
I'LL BE FREE.

05:21.408 --> 05:24.454
I'LL GET MY OWN APARTMENT,
WE'LL BE INSEPARABLE.

05:27.718 --> 05:29.067
I'M SORRY, LOGAN.

05:30.765 --> 05:31.679
WHAT'S THIS?

05:31.809 --> 05:33.985
CAROLINE, I LOVE YOU.

05:37.728 --> 05:38.990
KEEP THE RING.

05:40.035 --> 05:41.123
I CAN'T.

05:43.299 --> 05:45.040
I CAN'T DO THIS ANYMORE, LOGAN.

05:45.170 --> 05:47.085
I CAN'T LIVE
ON HOPES AND DREAMS ANYMORE.

05:59.446 --> 06:00.577
HEY.

06:01.839 --> 06:03.580
I GUESS YOU TALKED TO LOGAN.

06:06.453 --> 06:08.542
I KNOW HOW YOU MUST FEEL.

06:08.672 --> 06:10.370
BUT YOU DID THE RIGHT THING.

06:11.893 --> 06:13.068
YEAH.

06:14.896 --> 06:16.898
YEAH, IT WAS
THE MOST SENSIBLE THING TO DO.

06:18.203 --> 06:19.814
I MEAN, YOU CAN'T CARRY ON

06:19.944 --> 06:21.816
A MEANINGFUL RELATIONSHIP
WITH A MARRIED MAN.

06:23.557 --> 06:25.646
NOT UNLESS
YOU'RE MARRIED TO HIM.

06:27.952 --> 06:30.346
EVEN THEN THERE'S
NO GUARANTEES, RIGHT?

06:31.826 --> 06:32.827
RIGHT.

06:38.485 --> 06:40.704
OH, MITCH, HOLD ON ONE SECOND.
I WANT TO ASK YOU A QUESTION.

06:40.835 --> 06:42.924
-THANKS FOR THE TALK.
-BYE, HAVE A GOOD DAY.

06:43.054 --> 06:44.316
MORNING.

06:44.447 --> 06:46.014
I HAD A QUESTION
ABOUT TOWER ASSIGNMENTS.

06:46.144 --> 06:47.755
WHO'S A.J. ON TOWER 12?

06:47.885 --> 06:49.713
ANDY JAMISON, REMEMBER
I TOLD YOU ABOUT HIM.

06:49.844 --> 06:51.889
HE CALLED AND ASKED IF WE
COULD FIT HIM INTO ROTATION.

06:52.020 --> 06:53.674
HE NEEDS HIS FOUR DAYS
TO STAY ON THE ACTIVE LIST.

06:53.804 --> 06:55.458
ARE YOU SURE
HE CAN HANDLE TOWER 12?

06:55.589 --> 06:57.417
I MEAN THAT'S A REALLY
HECTIC BEACH FOR A PART-TIMER.

06:57.547 --> 06:59.331
HE'S AN OLD PRO,
HE KNOWS HIS STUFF.

07:15.565 --> 07:17.132
[LAUGHING]

07:17.262 --> 07:19.003
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
CHECKING UP ON ME ALREADY?

07:19.134 --> 07:20.614
ABSOLUTELY, MAN, HOW YOU DOING?

07:20.744 --> 07:22.616
OH, WHAT IS THIS, LOOK
AT ALL THIS FLAB MAN.

07:22.746 --> 07:25.096
-WHEN ARE YOU GETTING IN SHAPE?
-HEY, I'M WORKING ON IT.

07:25.227 --> 07:28.273
OH, THIS IS MY CO-COMMANDER,
LIEUTENANT HOLDEN.

07:28.404 --> 07:29.405
-STEPHANIE.
-ANDY.

07:29.536 --> 07:30.624
NICE TO MEET YOU.

07:30.754 --> 07:32.190
THANKS A LOT FOR BRINGING ME ON.

07:32.321 --> 07:34.062
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU WORKED A TOWER?

07:34.192 --> 07:35.933
LAST YEAR UP AT TRANKIS.

07:36.064 --> 07:38.719
I WISH I COULD DO MORE, BUT
MY DAY JOB KEEPS ME PRETTY BUSY.

07:38.849 --> 07:40.024
WHAT DO YOU DO?

07:40.155 --> 07:41.722
I'M A SHERIFF UP
IN VENTURA COUNTY.

07:42.505 --> 07:43.811
SHERIFF, REALLY?

07:43.941 --> 07:45.769
WHAT, YOU WANNA SEE MY BADGE?

07:46.857 --> 07:48.772
NO, NO, NO, I BELIEVE YOU.

07:49.730 --> 07:51.688
SO HOW'S IT FEEL TO HAVE
YOUR FEET BACK IN THE SAND?

07:51.819 --> 07:53.995
OH, IT MAKES ME WONDER
WHY I EVER GAVE IT UP.

07:54.125 --> 07:55.431
THE PAY STINKS.

07:55.953 --> 07:57.085
OH YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

07:58.303 --> 08:00.088
STILL THE BEST OFFICE
IN THE WORLD.

08:00.828 --> 08:02.525
-THANKS.
-WELCOME.

08:04.440 --> 08:05.702
THOUGHT THEY WEREN'T GONNA LET

08:05.833 --> 08:07.487
THESE BUMS SLEEP
ON THE BEACH ANYMORE?

08:09.445 --> 08:11.055
WELL, WHERE ELSE
ARE THEY SUPPOSED TO GO?

08:11.186 --> 08:13.144
THEY JUST BUILT A NEW SHELTER
IN SANTA MONICA.

08:13.275 --> 08:14.798
IT'S HALF EMPTY EVERY NIGHT.

08:14.929 --> 08:16.321
THOSE GUYS AREN'T INTERESTED

08:16.452 --> 08:18.019
IN HAVING A ROOF
OVER THEIR HEADS, THE ONLY THING

08:18.149 --> 08:19.760
THEY'RE INTERESTED IN
IS GETTING LOADED.

08:19.890 --> 08:21.762
HEY, HEY, HEY, TAKE IT EASY,
MAN, THEY'RE HARMLESS.

08:26.506 --> 08:27.419
CATCH YOU GUYS LATER.

08:27.550 --> 08:28.769
ALL RIGHT.

08:30.684 --> 08:31.902
HOW WELL DO YOU KNOW ANDY?

08:32.033 --> 08:34.208
WE USED TO HANG TOGETHER
IN THE OLD DAYS.

08:35.905 --> 08:37.647
I HAVEN'T SEEN HIM
IN A COUPLE YEARS.

08:40.563 --> 08:41.695
YOU DON'T LIKE HIM, HUH?

08:41.825 --> 08:43.697
I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

08:43.827 --> 08:45.742
WHY, BECAUSE HE'S NOT SENSITIVE
TO THE PLIGHT OF THE HOMELESS?

08:45.873 --> 08:47.831
LOOK, HE'S ENTITLED
TO HIS OPINION.

08:48.353 --> 08:49.572
SO WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

08:50.312 --> 08:51.879
WELL, HE ONLY WORKS
FOUR DAYS A YEAR,

08:52.009 --> 08:53.620
HE'S BOUND TO BE RUSTY.

08:56.231 --> 08:57.101
RIGHT?

08:59.190 --> 09:02.542
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

09:52.679 --> 09:54.681
-MOMMY!
-THERE SHE IS!

09:56.987 --> 09:57.814
THANK YOU!

10:13.308 --> 10:14.831
SO, HAS HE PASSED THE AUDITION?

10:17.399 --> 10:18.835
HE'S A GOOD LIFEGUARD.

10:21.795 --> 10:23.623
WHAT ARE YOU DOING,
FOLLOWING ME?

10:26.669 --> 10:28.497
I HATE TO SAY I TOLD YOU SO.

10:29.411 --> 10:32.632
WELL, IT'S NOT LIKE I NEVER
MISJUDGED A MAN BEFORE.

10:37.898 --> 10:40.074
SURE BEATS THE HELL
OUT OF SOUTH DAKOTA.

10:40.204 --> 10:41.728
IF WE WERE BACK HOME RIGHT NOW,

10:41.858 --> 10:44.731
WE'D BE SHOVELING SNOW,
FREEZING OUR BUNS OFF.

10:44.861 --> 10:46.689
I'M NEVER GOING BACK.

10:51.738 --> 10:53.348
UNLESS SHE COMES BACK WITH ME.

10:53.478 --> 10:55.306
OH MAN, LOOK AT THAT BODY.

10:55.437 --> 10:58.309
YES, AND SHE WILL BE MINE,
OH YES, SHE WILL BE MINE.

11:00.572 --> 11:03.097
[LAUGHTING]

11:04.098 --> 11:07.101
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

11:18.460 --> 11:19.853
HEY, WHAT THE...

11:21.419 --> 11:22.769
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM, MAN?

11:22.899 --> 11:24.727
CAN EITHER OF YOUR MORONS READ?

11:24.858 --> 11:27.512
THE SIGN SAYS NO ALCOHOLIC
BEVERAGES ON THE BEACH.

11:30.428 --> 11:31.516
DON'T YOU GUYS HAVE
ANYTHING ELSE BETTER

11:31.647 --> 11:32.692
TO DO THAN DRINK ALL DAY?

11:32.822 --> 11:34.302
WHAT DO YOU CARE, MAN?

11:34.432 --> 11:36.434
I'M LOOKING OUT
FOR YOUR WELL-BEING, FRIEND.

11:38.001 --> 11:39.307
WHAT ELSE YOU GOT IN HERE?

11:39.437 --> 11:40.264
MAN, YOU GOT NO RIGHT
TO SEARCH US.

11:40.395 --> 11:42.876
[GRUNTING]

11:48.751 --> 11:50.884
YOU MADE YOUR POINT,
WE'RE OUT OF HERE.

11:51.014 --> 11:52.581
GOOD, AND IN THE FUTURE

11:52.712 --> 11:54.148
I DON'T WANT TO SEE YOU
ON MY BEACH AGAIN.

11:54.278 --> 11:55.105
YOU GOT THAT?

11:55.236 --> 11:56.106
YEAH.

11:57.238 --> 11:58.587
WHAT'D YOU SAY, HUH?

12:01.285 --> 12:03.157
LET HIM GO, WE'RE SORRY.

12:03.287 --> 12:04.419
WE DON'T WANT ANY HASSLES.

12:04.549 --> 12:05.942
JUST BE COOL, OKAY?

12:07.248 --> 12:09.380
HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

12:09.511 --> 12:11.121
THESE GENTLEMEN
WERE CONSUMING ALCOHOL

12:11.252 --> 12:13.602
ON A COUNTY BEACH, LIEUTENANT,
THAT'S A MISDEMEANOR.

12:13.733 --> 12:15.386
UNLESS THEY'RE REPEAT OFFENDERS,

12:15.517 --> 12:17.432
IN WHICH CASE THEY'RE LOOKING
AT A LITTLE JAIL TIME.

12:18.041 --> 12:19.173
LET HIM GO.

12:21.088 --> 12:22.045
NOW!

12:26.920 --> 12:28.748
COME ON MAN,
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE!

12:28.965 --> 12:30.488
HE'S CRAZY.

12:30.619 --> 12:32.664
WHERE DO YOU GET OFF
TREATING PEOPLE LIKE THAT?

12:32.795 --> 12:34.449
THEY WERE BREAKING THE LAW.

12:34.579 --> 12:37.278
WHEN YOU GET OFF-DUTY,
I WANNA SEE YOU IN MY OFFICE.

12:45.852 --> 12:47.592
LOOK, MITCH,
I KNOW HE'S YOUR FRIEND AND ALL,

12:47.723 --> 12:49.638
BUT ANDY JUST SEEMS
A LITTLE OUT OF CONTROL.

12:49.769 --> 12:51.118
I MEAN IF I HADN'T SHOWN UP,

12:51.248 --> 12:52.684
WELL, WHO KNOWS
WHAT MIGHT HAVE HAPPENED.

12:52.815 --> 12:54.556
HE LOOKED LIKE HE REALLY
WANTED TO HURT THEM.

12:56.210 --> 12:58.299
I WANT YOU IN ON THIS MEETING
WHEN ANDY GETS HERE.

12:58.429 --> 12:59.953
HE NEEDS TO HEAR IT
FROM BOTH OF US.

13:00.692 --> 13:01.650
HEAR WHAT?

13:01.781 --> 13:03.391
THAT LIFEGUARDS AREN'T COPS.

13:03.521 --> 13:04.871
[ANDY] THANKS FOR THE RIDE.

13:05.001 --> 13:07.003
[WOMAN] OKAY ANDY, ANYTIME.

13:07.134 --> 13:09.005
YOU READY TO HEAR
MY SIDE OF THE STORY,

13:09.136 --> 13:11.051
OR HAVE I ALREADY BEEN
TRIED AND CONVICTED?

13:12.008 --> 13:13.793
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
WHAT HAPPENED?

13:13.923 --> 13:16.056
COUPLE OF DIRT BAGS
WERE DRINKING ON THE BEACH,

13:16.186 --> 13:18.275
WHEN I WENT TO TAKE THEIR BOTTLE
AWAY THEY JUMPED ME.

13:19.233 --> 13:21.496
FORTUNATELY I WAS ABLE
TO DEFEND MYSELF.

13:21.626 --> 13:24.368
DEFEND YOURSELF? YOU HAD
ONE OF THEM IN A CHOKE HOLD.

13:24.978 --> 13:26.718
THAT WAS NOT
A CHOKE HOLD, LIEUTENANT.

13:26.849 --> 13:28.808
HE WOULDN'T HAVE BEEN BREATHING
IF THAT WAS A CHOKE HOLD.

13:28.938 --> 13:31.767
I DON'T KNOW IF YOU'RE AWARE
OF IT, BUT OVER 50 LIFEGUARDS

13:31.898 --> 13:33.421
HAVE EITHER BEEN ASSAULTED

13:33.551 --> 13:35.162
OR SERIOUSLY THREATENED
IN THE LAST TWO YEARS.

13:36.076 --> 13:37.817
I KNOW THE STATISTICS,
THANK YOU.

13:39.122 --> 13:41.124
I KNOW I'M ONLY GONNA BE HERE
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS,

13:41.255 --> 13:43.170
BUT I DON'T INTEND
ON BECOMING A VICTIM.

13:43.300 --> 13:45.955
SO YOUR ATTITUDE IS TO GET THEM
BEFORE THEY GET US.

13:46.086 --> 13:47.391
MY ATTITUDE IS DON'T TAKE

13:47.522 --> 13:49.132
YOUR PERSONAL SAFETY
FOR GRANTED.

13:49.263 --> 13:51.569
ESPECIALLY WHEN YOU'RE OUT THERE
IN YOUR UNDERWEAR

13:51.700 --> 13:54.137
OVERSEEING A BEACH
FULL OF POTENTIAL CRAZIES.

13:54.268 --> 13:55.791
YOU'VE GOTTA BE PREPARED

13:55.922 --> 13:57.445
TO DEAL WITH WHAT WE'RE
UP AGAINST THESE DAYS.

13:57.575 --> 13:59.664
LET ME GIVE YOU AN EXAMPLE
OF WHAT I MEAN, MITCH.

13:59.795 --> 14:01.928
EVERY LIFEGUARD TRUCK
IS SUPPOSED TO BE EQUIPPED

14:02.058 --> 14:03.407
WITH A PAIR OF HANDCUFFS, RIGHT?

14:04.278 --> 14:07.281
NOW, I'LL JUST BET THAT
THAT WAS NOT ON THE TOP

14:07.411 --> 14:09.849
OF LIEUTENANT HOLDEN'S LIST
OF PRIORITIES THIS MORNING.

14:15.506 --> 14:16.768
I STAND CORRECTED.

14:17.987 --> 14:19.249
ALL RIGHT,
NOW THE QUESTION BECOMES,

14:19.380 --> 14:20.729
DO YOU KNOW HOW TO USE THEM?

14:20.860 --> 14:22.296
WELL, I'VE NEVER HAD
TO USE THEM,

14:22.426 --> 14:24.515
BECAUSE WHEN I SEE
TROUBLE I CALL THE POLICE.

14:24.646 --> 14:25.821
WELL, WHAT IF YOU DON'T
HAVE TIME,

14:25.952 --> 14:27.127
OR THERE'S NOT A COP AROUND?

14:27.997 --> 14:29.651
THESE COULD
SAVE YOUR LIFE SOMEDAY,

14:29.781 --> 14:31.696
AND WITH THE PROPER TRAINING
YOU'D BE SURPRISED

14:31.827 --> 14:34.482
HOW EASY IT IS TO SLAP THEM
ON SOMEBODY TWICE YOUR SIZE.

14:37.137 --> 14:38.138
SEE WHAT I MEAN?

14:40.096 --> 14:42.794
VERY FUNNY, GET 'EM OFF.

14:42.925 --> 14:44.579
I HOPE YOU HAVE
THE KEY IN THERE, TOO.

14:47.799 --> 14:49.105
SORRY ABOUT THAT, MITCH.

14:49.236 --> 14:50.324
NOT TOO TIGHT ARE THEY?

14:51.368 --> 14:53.022
I THINK YOU MADE YOUR POINT.

15:00.987 --> 15:01.901
[KNOCKING]

15:04.294 --> 15:05.339
COMING.

15:15.740 --> 15:17.003
[KNOCKING]

15:18.656 --> 15:20.441
ALL RIGHT, HOLD YOUR HORSES.

15:29.929 --> 15:31.147
HI.

15:33.758 --> 15:34.934
CAN I COME IN?

15:36.761 --> 15:38.763
I DON'T THINK THAT WOULD BE
A VERY GOOD IDEA.

15:39.677 --> 15:41.114
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

15:41.766 --> 15:43.377
SO TALK.

15:43.507 --> 15:45.509
I THINK YOU SHOULD BE SITTING
DOWN WHEN YOU HEAR THIS.

15:46.293 --> 15:47.859
PLEASE DON'T PLAY GAMES
WITH ME, LOGAN.

15:50.036 --> 15:51.951
I'VE HAD MY MARRIAGE ANNULLED.

15:54.388 --> 15:55.606
YOU WHAT?

15:56.912 --> 15:58.522
DOES THIS MEAN I CAN COME IN?

16:15.017 --> 16:18.673
SO, YOU SAY YOU'RE HAVING
YOUR MARRIAGE ANNULLED.

16:18.803 --> 16:21.197
NOT HAVING, HAD,
IT'S A DONE DEAL.

16:22.503 --> 16:23.460
I'M SINGLE AGAIN.

16:25.506 --> 16:26.855
SO WHAT DOES THIS MEAN?

16:29.249 --> 16:30.990
ARE YOU GONNA GO BACK
TO AUSTRALIA?

16:31.642 --> 16:32.948
PROBABLY.

16:35.429 --> 16:37.779
BUT AT LEAST
WE'LL BE TOGETHER TIL THEN.

16:41.435 --> 16:42.914
WILL YOU TAKE THIS BACK?

16:59.018 --> 17:00.193
AUSTRIA.

17:00.410 --> 17:02.325
UH, VIENNA.

17:03.283 --> 17:04.240
NEPAL.

17:05.894 --> 17:06.721
KATHMANDU.

17:06.851 --> 17:08.069
GOT IT, HUNGARY.

17:09.637 --> 17:13.336
UH, BUCHAREST,
NO, NO, NO WAIT, BUDAPEST.

17:13.467 --> 17:14.598
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL GIVE YOU THAT ONE.

17:14.729 --> 17:15.643
MALAYSIA.

17:15.772 --> 17:17.992
MALAYSIA, MALAYSIA.

17:18.559 --> 17:20.039
KUALA LUMPUR.

17:20.169 --> 17:22.127
KUALA LUMPUR IT IS,
WINNER, WINNER, WINNER.

17:22.258 --> 17:24.042
FINALLY, THAT'S 20 OUT OF 20,
CAN I GO NOW?

17:24.173 --> 17:25.261
YEAH, GET OUT OF HERE
AND HAVE FUN, HUH?

17:25.392 --> 17:26.262
THANKS.

17:29.135 --> 17:30.919
YOU'VE GOTTA BE HOBIE.

17:31.050 --> 17:32.094
UH, YEAH.

17:32.225 --> 17:33.661
YOU PROBABLY DON'T REMEMBER ME,

17:33.791 --> 17:34.749
I'M AN OLD FRIEND
OF YOUR DAD'S, ANDY JAMISON.

17:34.879 --> 17:36.446
HI.

17:36.577 --> 17:38.535
LAST TIME I SAW YOU,
YOU WERE UP TO MY KNEECAPS.

17:38.666 --> 17:40.276
TAKING GOOD CARE
OF YOUR OLD MAN?

17:40.407 --> 17:43.236
YEAH, HE'S A PAIN SOMETIMES,
BUT WE GET ALONG OKAY.

17:44.237 --> 17:45.586
CHIP OFF THE OLD BLOCK, MITCH.

17:45.716 --> 17:46.804
YEAH.

17:47.283 --> 17:49.503
ALL RIGHT, WELL I GOTTA GO,
SEE YOU LATER.

17:50.156 --> 17:51.244
YOU BET.

17:54.247 --> 17:56.771
HEY, MITCH, I WANNA
APOLOGIZE FOR YESTERDAY.

17:56.901 --> 17:59.382
I GUESS I THOUGHT
I WAS STILL ON THE STREET.

17:59.513 --> 18:01.036
YOU KNOW HOW IT IS,
FIRST DAY BACK,

18:01.167 --> 18:02.951
TAKES A LITTLE WHILE
TO MELLOW OUT.

18:03.778 --> 18:05.823
YOU KNOW, ANDY, WE ALL HAVE
OUR SHARE OF PROBLEMS OUT THERE,

18:05.954 --> 18:08.565
BUT MOST PEOPLE STILL COME TO
THE BEACH TO HAVE A GOOD TIME.

18:09.305 --> 18:10.306
I HEAR YA.

18:11.394 --> 18:13.744
SO, NO HARD FEELINGS?

18:13.875 --> 18:15.877
I WOULDN'T TAKE IT THAT FAR.

18:16.007 --> 18:18.314
I BETTER GET OUT TO MY TOWER.

18:18.445 --> 18:19.750
KEEP YOUR EYE ON YOUR WATER.

18:20.708 --> 18:22.231
YOU BET.

18:22.362 --> 18:23.624
HEY, MITCH, AFTER WORK
YOU WANNA GET A BEER?

18:23.754 --> 18:25.365
GOT A LOT OF CATCHING UP TO DO.

18:25.495 --> 18:26.888
YEAH, YEAH, WE DO.

18:27.018 --> 18:29.238
UM, BUT I CAN'T MAKE IT
TONIGHT, SORRY.

18:29.369 --> 18:31.719
WELL, WHENEVER YOU HAVE TIME,
JUST LET ME KNOW.

18:31.849 --> 18:33.416
AND THANKS AGAIN,

18:33.547 --> 18:34.852
YOU KNOW I REALLY APPRECIATE
YOU HELPING ME OUT.

18:39.074 --> 18:39.944
OKAY.

18:55.308 --> 18:57.310
GOT A COUPLE OF MESSAGES
FOR YOU, LIEUTENANT.

18:57.440 --> 18:59.094
-HERE YOU GO.
-THANKS, RON.

19:06.754 --> 19:08.059
LOGAN.

19:08.190 --> 19:10.453
GOOD AFTERNOON, LIEUTENANT.

19:11.585 --> 19:12.760
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME?

19:13.630 --> 19:14.414
IF THAT'S OKAY.

19:15.893 --> 19:16.851
WHAT'S ON YOUR MIND?

19:18.244 --> 19:19.375
QUITE A LOT ACTUALLY.

19:20.637 --> 19:22.552
I'M NOT SURE
WHAT CAROLINE'S TOLD YOU.

19:22.813 --> 19:24.859
SHE TOLD ME THAT SHE DIDN'T
WANT TO SEE YOU ANYMORE.

19:24.989 --> 19:26.643
THAT WAS WHEN I WAS MARRIED.

19:27.818 --> 19:29.516
WHICH IS NO LONGER THE CASE.

19:32.345 --> 19:35.174
MY MARRIAGE TO KATHLEEN
WAS ONE OF CONVENIENCE,

19:36.305 --> 19:39.090
SO I COULD BECOME A LEGAL
RESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES.

19:41.092 --> 19:44.313
THE TRUTH IS,
I'M IN LOVE WITH CAROLINE,

19:44.444 --> 19:46.620
AND UNLESS I'M SORELY MISTAKEN
SHE'S IN LOVE WITH ME.

19:46.750 --> 19:48.535
WHY ARE YOU
TELLING ME THIS, LOGAN?

19:51.102 --> 19:52.278
BECAUSE UM...

19:56.020 --> 19:58.066
'CAUSE I NEED YOUR HELP.

19:59.589 --> 20:01.852
I CAN ONLY REMAIN
IN THE COUNTRY IF MY SERVICES

20:01.983 --> 20:04.203
ARE CONSIDERED ESSENTIAL
TO MY EMPLOYER.

20:06.335 --> 20:10.078
IF YOU TOLD THE INS THAT I'M
A PERSON OF EXCEPTIONAL SKILL,

20:11.122 --> 20:12.689
THAT'LL GIVE ME MY GREEN CARD.

20:15.866 --> 20:18.739
SO, I'LL DETERMINE
WHETHER OR NOT

20:18.869 --> 20:20.436
YOU GO BACK TO AUSTRALIA.

20:20.567 --> 20:23.309
I REALIZE THAT'S BEEN
A LONG-TIME GOAL OF YOURS,

20:24.048 --> 20:25.615
BUT FOR YOUR SISTER'S SAKE...

20:26.486 --> 20:27.791
I'LL THINK ABOUT IT.

20:28.444 --> 20:30.490
I NEED TO GET THE PAPERWORK
DONE AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

20:32.622 --> 20:34.233
I'LL GIVE YOU
AN ANSWER TOMORROW.

20:36.409 --> 20:37.845
THANK YOU FOR YOUR TIME,
LIEUTENANT.

20:37.975 --> 20:39.586
YOU'RE WELCOME, LOGAN.

21:11.835 --> 21:14.098
[PHONE RINGING]

21:14.838 --> 21:15.709
TOWER FOUR.

21:15.839 --> 21:17.319
HEY, STEPH, YOU READY?

21:18.059 --> 21:19.974
THANKS, MITCH,
BUT I THINK I'M GONNA RUN BACK.

21:20.104 --> 21:21.758
I NEED THE WORKOUT.

21:21.889 --> 21:23.891
IT'S GETTING DARK SOON,
YOU CAN WORK OUT IN THE MORNING.

21:24.021 --> 21:26.720
MITCH, I'LL SEE YOU BACK
AT HEADQUARTERS, ALRIGHT?

21:26.850 --> 21:28.287
HEY, HEY, HEY, WAIT A MINUTE,

21:28.417 --> 21:30.245
I'LL BE THERE IN FIVE MINUTES,
HANG ON.

21:48.916 --> 21:50.744
LET'S THINK ABOUT THIS
FOR A MINUTE.

21:50.874 --> 21:52.702
WHAT'S THERE TO THINK ABOUT?

21:52.833 --> 21:55.052
YOU WANT TO KEEP SLEEPING IN
A SANDOMINIUM OR START STYLIN'?

21:55.183 --> 21:56.924
COME ON,
DON'T WUSS OUT ON ME, DONNIE,

21:57.054 --> 21:57.881
GET YOUR BUTT OUT HERE!

22:07.282 --> 22:08.936
HEY! HEY!

22:09.937 --> 22:11.634
HEY, LIFEGUARD, OVER HERE!

22:12.722 --> 22:14.333
ALL RIGHT, GET READY,
HERE HE COMES.

22:16.422 --> 22:18.206
LIFEGUARD, OVER HERE!

22:18.337 --> 22:19.729
I NEED SOME HELP, HURRY!

22:19.860 --> 22:21.340
COME ON! COME ON!

22:25.344 --> 22:26.736
WHAT HAPPENED?

22:26.867 --> 22:28.999
HE MUST HAVE OD'ED OR SOMETHING.

22:31.132 --> 22:34.178
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

22:40.576 --> 22:41.490
PUT IT DOWN!

22:42.186 --> 22:43.579
MOVE AWAY FROM THE TRUCK.

22:43.710 --> 22:45.364
GOOD, NOW GET YOUR HANDS
UP WHERE I CAN SEE THEM.

22:49.716 --> 22:52.849
[GROANING]

22:59.290 --> 23:01.336
GET UP, COME ON,
MOVE IT, LET'S GO.

23:01.467 --> 23:03.817
WE GOTTA GET OUT OF HERE, MAN,
BEFORE ANYONE ELSE COMES.

23:31.192 --> 23:33.063
HI, THIS IS STEPHANIE
FROM TOWER FOUR.

23:33.194 --> 23:35.283
CAN YOU RING MITCH'S
TOWER FOR ME? HE'S AT 10.

23:35.414 --> 23:37.459
NO PROBLEM, LIEUTENANT,
I'LL GET HIM RIGHT AWAY.

23:40.593 --> 23:42.638
[PHONE RINGING]

23:49.384 --> 23:50.429
NO ANSWER.

23:51.168 --> 23:53.910
-TRY HIS TRUCK.
-HOLD ON.

23:55.216 --> 23:56.435
MITCH, COME IN.

23:59.307 --> 24:00.395
COME IN, MITCH.

24:01.614 --> 24:03.050
HE'S NOT RESPONDING.

24:03.180 --> 24:06.357
[HORN HONKING]

24:15.062 --> 24:17.064
SEND BACKUP
TO HIS TOWER RIGHT AWAY!

24:17.194 --> 24:20.459
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

24:24.201 --> 24:27.770
[SIRENS]

24:31.513 --> 24:34.908
MITCH! MITCH, WHAT HAPPENED?

24:35.038 --> 24:36.649
THEY STOLE MY TRUCK.

24:36.779 --> 24:38.302
DON'T GET UP, DON'T GET UP.

24:38.999 --> 24:40.479
IS HE OKAY?

24:40.609 --> 24:42.437
OH, YOU GOT ONE HECK
OF A BUMP ON YOUR HEAD.

24:42.568 --> 24:44.352
GET US A BACKBOARD, OKAY?

24:45.484 --> 24:47.311
I'M OKAY,
I DON'T NEED A BACKBOARD.

24:47.442 --> 24:48.574
MITCH.

24:48.704 --> 24:50.097
[GROANING]

24:50.227 --> 24:51.359
BETTER GET A BACKBOARD.

24:52.795 --> 24:56.451
[GROANING]

25:03.153 --> 25:04.720
I STILL THINK YOU SHOULD GO
TO THE HOSPITAL,

25:04.851 --> 25:06.766
YOU MIGHT HAVE A CONCUSSION
OR NERVE DAMAGE.

25:06.896 --> 25:09.290
ALL RIGHT, JUST TAKE
THIS ICE PACK AT LEAST.

25:09.420 --> 25:11.640
[CLAPPING]

25:11.771 --> 25:13.337
WHAT? WHAT?

25:13.468 --> 25:15.470
IT'S ONLY A BUMP ON THE HEAD.

25:16.689 --> 25:18.691
MITCH, DO YOU HAVE
ANY IDEA HOW LUCKY YOU ARE?

25:18.821 --> 25:19.953
YOU COULD'VE BEEN SHOT.

25:21.128 --> 25:22.782
THE POLICE JUST CALLED,

25:22.912 --> 25:25.088
A BEACH PARKING ATTENDANT
WAS HELD UP BY TWO LIFEGUARDS.

25:25.219 --> 25:26.220
WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON?

25:26.350 --> 25:27.961
MITCH WAS JUST CARJACKED.

25:28.091 --> 25:29.397
YOU'RE KIDDING.

25:29.528 --> 25:31.007
DID THEY CATCH
THE GUYS WHO DID IT?

25:31.138 --> 25:32.269
NO, BUT THEY'RE GONNA CALL BACK

25:32.400 --> 25:33.532
WHEN THEY FIND OUT WHO DID.

25:33.662 --> 25:35.229
MAYBE WE SHOULD GO LEND A HAND.

25:35.359 --> 25:37.666
OH NO, YOU GUYS KNOW
THAT'S NOT GONNA SOLVE ANYTHING.

25:37.797 --> 25:39.668
WELL, I THINK
WHAT EVERYONE'S UPSET ABOUT

25:39.799 --> 25:42.149
IS WHAT HAPPENED TO MITCH COULD
HAPPEN TO ANY ONE OF YOU.

25:42.279 --> 25:44.368
YOUR PEOPLE NEED A BASIC
COURSE IN SELF-DEFENSE.

25:44.499 --> 25:45.979
ANDY, ALL OUR LIFEGUARDS RECEIVE

25:46.632 --> 25:48.503
SELF-DEFENSE TRAINING
IN ROOKIE SCHOOL.

25:48.634 --> 25:51.375
WELL, LIEUTENANT,
IT WASN'T THAT EXTENSIVE.

25:51.506 --> 25:53.813
I KNOW I FOR ONE WOULD FEEL
A LOT MORE CONFIDENT

25:53.943 --> 25:55.162
IF I HAD A REFRESHER COURSE.

25:55.292 --> 25:56.685
ESPECIALLY AFTER
WHAT JUST HAPPENED.

25:56.816 --> 25:58.687
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,
I'LL CONDUCT A CLINIC

25:58.818 --> 26:00.515
FOR ANYONE WHO NEEDS
ADDITIONAL TRAINING.

26:00.646 --> 26:01.908
IT'S OKAY WITH ME.

26:03.344 --> 26:06.303
WELL, IF IT'S VOLUNTARY, THERE'S
NOTHING I CAN DO ABOUT IT.

26:07.435 --> 26:09.306
OKAY, ON THE BEACH IN 15.

26:09.437 --> 26:11.918
A LIFEGUARD'S
FIRST LINE OF DEFENSE

26:12.048 --> 26:14.616
IS HIS OR HER RESCUE CAN.

26:14.877 --> 26:17.837
IT'S VERSATILE,
HIGHLY FUNCTIONAL,

26:17.967 --> 26:20.666
AND DESIGNED TO SAVE LIVES
IN AND OUT OF THE WATER.

26:20.796 --> 26:22.711
LIEUTENANT BUCHANNON'S
FIRST MISTAKE

26:22.842 --> 26:25.409
WAS APPROACHING
A VICTIM WITHOUT THIS DEVICE.

26:25.932 --> 26:29.588
HE LEFT HIMSELF UNPROTECTED,
AND EXTREMELY VULNERABLE.

26:29.718 --> 26:31.938
IN MY OPINION,
HE'S FORTUNATE TO BE ALIVE.

26:32.068 --> 26:35.506
NOW, I'M GONNA BE TEACHING
A WIDE RANGE OF TECHNIQUES,

26:36.159 --> 26:39.946
SO STAY FOCUSED, 'CAUSE THE LIFE
YOU SAVE MAY BE YOUR OWN.

