[GRUNTING]

29:30.769 --> 29:32.379
[GASPING]

29:37.297 --> 29:38.864
HELP! HELP!

29:39.560 --> 29:43.694
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

29:54.662 --> 29:55.663
HELP!

30:00.363 --> 30:02.104
OKAY, I GOT YA.

30:02.583 --> 30:03.497
WHAT HAPPENED?

30:03.627 --> 30:05.368
THERE'S A CRAMP IN MY LEG.

30:05.499 --> 30:07.196
JUST RELAX, YOU'LL BE FINE.

30:07.457 --> 30:10.939
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

30:12.462 --> 30:14.769
[SIRENS]

30:23.386 --> 30:25.127
GET A BLANKET OUT OF MY TOWER!

30:25.258 --> 30:26.346
YOU GOT IT.

30:35.921 --> 30:39.794
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

30:51.937 --> 30:53.982
STAY WRAPPED UP IN THAT BLANKET
UNTIL YOU GET WARM.

30:54.113 --> 30:55.592
I'LL BE DOWN TO GET IT
BEFORE YOU LEAVE.

30:57.029 --> 30:59.379
HEY, ANDY, COME HERE
FOR A SECOND, WILL YA?

31:03.122 --> 31:04.950
I WANT YOU PACKED UP
AND OFF THE BEACH.

31:06.212 --> 31:07.213
THAT'S A DIRECT ORDER.

31:07.343 --> 31:08.692
WHY? WHAT DID I DO?

31:11.086 --> 31:12.522
CROSSED THE LINE.

31:12.653 --> 31:14.176
MITCH, I'M AUTHORIZED
TO CARRY A HANDGUN.

31:14.307 --> 31:17.005
AS A SHERIFF MAYBE,
BUT NOT AS A LIFEGUARD.

31:18.137 --> 31:19.703
WHAT IF SOMEBODY

31:19.834 --> 31:21.053
WENT INTO YOUR TOWER
WHILE YOU WERE IN THE WATER?

31:21.183 --> 31:22.663
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING HERE?

31:22.793 --> 31:24.752
I WAS THINKING SOMEBODY
PULLED A GUN ON YOU,

31:24.883 --> 31:27.059
AND THE ONLY WAY
TO FIGHT FIRE IS WITH FIRE.

31:27.189 --> 31:29.278
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU ANYWAY?

31:32.325 --> 31:33.979
YOU DIDN'T USED TO BE LIKE THIS.

31:35.371 --> 31:36.720
WHY WERE YOU PULLED OFF
THE STREET?

31:36.851 --> 31:38.070
IS THAT WHAT THIS IS ALL ABOUT?

31:40.594 --> 31:41.943
I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU REMEMBER MY WIFE,

31:42.074 --> 31:43.597
SHE USED TO HANG OUT AT MY TOWER

31:43.727 --> 31:45.207
WHEN SHE WAS IN HIGH SCHOOL,
THAT'S HOW WE MET.

31:45.338 --> 31:47.731
YEAH, OF COURSE
I REMEMBER YOUR WIFE, BECKY.

31:51.474 --> 31:53.476
BECKY WAS KILLED LAST YEAR.

31:56.784 --> 31:58.655
COUPLE OF PUNKS FOLLOWED
HER HOME FROM WORK,

32:00.048 --> 32:02.659
ROBBED THE HOUSE AND SHOT HER.

32:10.450 --> 32:15.150
I CAME HOME AND FOUND HER LYING
ON THE LIVING ROOM FLOOR.

32:20.547 --> 32:22.027
I'M SORRY.

32:25.465 --> 32:26.770
I WENT TO A POLICE PSYCHOLOGIST,

32:26.901 --> 32:28.337
BUT THAT DIDN'T DO ANY GOOD.

32:29.904 --> 32:31.819
NEVER GET THAT PICTURE
OUT OF MY MIND.

32:37.477 --> 32:40.132
LOOK, GET YOUR STUFF,
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

32:44.745 --> 32:46.660
OH MAN.

33:01.109 --> 33:02.197
HI.

33:02.981 --> 33:05.374
HOW COME YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
LOGAN HAD HIS MARRIAGE ANNULLED?

33:06.375 --> 33:07.855
WHAT DIFFERENCE
WOULD IT HAVE MADE?

33:07.986 --> 33:09.639
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE LET HIM STAY.

33:10.336 --> 33:12.512
WELL, IT'S NOT LIKE WE COULDN'T
DO VERY WELL WITHOUT HIM.

33:12.642 --> 33:14.079
COME OFF IT, STEPHANIE.

33:14.209 --> 33:15.819
YOU KNOW PERFECTLY WELL
THAT LOGAN

33:15.950 --> 33:17.691
IS ONE OF THE BEST LIFEGUARDS
WE HAVE AT BAYWATCH.

33:17.821 --> 33:19.649
YOU JUST DON'T WANT US
TO BE TOGETHER.

33:19.780 --> 33:22.217
-THAT IS NOT TRUE.
-YES, IT IS.

33:25.307 --> 33:27.266
YOU ALWAYS THINK
YOU KNOW WHAT'S BEST FOR ME.

33:28.223 --> 33:29.398
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

33:30.095 --> 33:31.357
I DON'T CARE WHAT YOU DO,

33:31.487 --> 33:33.402
BECAUSE IF LOGAN
GOES TO AUSTRALIA,

33:33.533 --> 33:35.448
I'M JUST GONNA GO WITH HIM.

33:59.428 --> 34:02.431
PLEASE GET AWAY FROM THERE,
THOSE ROCKS ARE DANGEROUS.

34:04.607 --> 34:06.957
[GIRL] BARRY, COME ON,
DIDN'T YOU HEAR WHAT SHE SAID?

34:07.088 --> 34:08.393
DON'T WORRY, IT'S COOL.

34:08.524 --> 34:11.745
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

34:19.187 --> 34:20.362
OH MY GOD.

34:20.493 --> 34:21.929
IT'S FUN. COME ON, YOU TRY IT.

34:33.723 --> 34:35.507
I'LL GO FIRST, FOLLOW ME DOWN.

34:40.165 --> 34:41.688
-WHAT'S WRONG?
-IT'S TOO SLIPPERY.

34:41.818 --> 34:45.213
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

34:45.953 --> 34:48.042
BARRY, NO!

34:48.303 --> 34:52.742
[YELLING]

34:57.791 --> 34:59.184
OH MY GOD, HE FELL!

35:00.185 --> 35:01.882
[GASPING]

35:02.012 --> 35:06.713
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

35:15.200 --> 35:18.159
[GROANING]

35:34.219 --> 35:35.437
HANG ON.

35:42.879 --> 35:44.098
THANKS, LOGAN.

35:55.240 --> 35:56.719
NOW THIS IS THE LIFE.

35:57.111 --> 35:58.460
YOU KNOW, I WAS THINKING.

35:58.591 --> 36:00.419
IT'S TOO BAD
THAT LIFEGUARD WE TOOK OUT

36:00.549 --> 36:02.247
WASN'T THE ONE
WHO'D BEEN HASSLING US.

36:02.377 --> 36:04.162
THAT WOULD HAVE BEEN
ICING ON THE CAKE.

36:08.688 --> 36:09.906
BUD, CHECK IT OUT.

36:12.344 --> 36:14.128
AIN'T SHE THE ONE
YOU WERE SO HOT FOR?

36:15.173 --> 36:16.261
YEAH.

36:17.218 --> 36:18.567
WHY DON'T YOU GO
AND TALK TO HER?

36:21.004 --> 36:21.918
YEAH.

36:25.357 --> 36:28.186
DAMN, SHE GOT AWAY.

36:28.316 --> 36:30.710
MAYBE SHE'LL TURN AROUND
AND COME BACK THIS WAY.

36:32.277 --> 36:34.061
THEN I'LL HAVE
TO BE READY FOR HER.

36:42.678 --> 36:45.725
SHE WILL BE MINE.
OH YES, SHE WILL BE MINE.

36:46.900 --> 36:51.383
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

37:06.136 --> 37:10.184
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

37:18.845 --> 37:20.238
HI.

37:21.413 --> 37:23.763
WE WERE WONDERING
IF YOU WANTED TO PARTY WITH US.

37:23.893 --> 37:24.981
I DON'T THINK SO.

37:25.112 --> 37:27.114
OH, WAIT A MINUTE!

37:27.245 --> 37:29.116
THAT'S TOO BAD.

37:30.378 --> 37:32.075
HEY, WHERE DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE GOING?

37:32.206 --> 37:33.990
WHAT? YOU CAN'T TALK TO US?

37:34.861 --> 37:36.210
WE'RE COOL GUYS.

37:38.081 --> 37:41.302
[GROANING]

38:04.369 --> 38:05.457
SO WE MEET AGAIN.

38:06.196 --> 38:07.763
LIFE'S FUNNY THAT WAY.

38:07.894 --> 38:09.896
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, MAN?

38:11.767 --> 38:13.813
WHERE'D YOU GET
THE CUTE CLOTHES, FELLAS?

38:13.943 --> 38:15.554
COME INTO SOME MONEY RECENTLY?

38:15.684 --> 38:17.817
[SIRENS]

38:19.122 --> 38:21.168
DON'T TELL ME
YOU'RE THE CARJACKERS.

38:25.259 --> 38:26.826
MITCH, GUESS WHO WE GOT HERE.

38:27.740 --> 38:29.307
THESE THE FELLAS
WHO STOLE YOUR TRUCK.

38:30.482 --> 38:31.570
AIN'T THAT RIGHT, GUYS?

38:34.094 --> 38:36.401
YOU WANNA GET A FEW LICKS IN
BEFORE I DO MY THING?

38:37.663 --> 38:39.099
GIVE ME THE GUN, ANDY.

38:39.229 --> 38:40.274
CAN'T DO THAT, MITCH.

38:40.405 --> 38:42.232
LIFEGUARDS CAN'T CARRY WEAPONS.

38:43.669 --> 38:46.149
THE IRONY IS,
IF LIEUTENANT HOLDEN

38:46.280 --> 38:48.543
WOULD'VE LET ME TAKE CARE
OF 'EM THE FIRST TIME,

38:48.674 --> 38:50.676
WE WOULDN'T EVEN BE HAVING
THIS CONVERSATION.

38:51.764 --> 38:54.636
ANDY, THESE AREN'T
THE GUYS WHO KILLED BECKY.

38:54.767 --> 38:56.072
I KNOW THAT.

38:57.726 --> 38:59.641
YOU DON'T NEED
THIS KIND OF SCUM ON THE BEACH.

39:02.862 --> 39:05.212
YOU DON'T NEED THE GUN,
NOW GIVE IT TO ME.

39:08.346 --> 39:09.521
I LOVED HER, MITCH.

39:11.958 --> 39:15.135
I KNOW YOU DID, PAL, BUT
I'M TELLING YOU NOTHING YOU DO

39:15.265 --> 39:16.484
IS GONNA BRING HER BACK.

39:17.442 --> 39:19.095
BECKY WAS ALL I HAD, MITCH.

39:20.314 --> 39:22.272
I'M WASHED UP,
I GOT NO LIFE ANYMORE.

39:22.403 --> 39:23.578
YES, YOU DO.

39:24.362 --> 39:25.493
NOW LOOK AT ME,

39:26.625 --> 39:29.236
YOU DO HAVE A LIFE, MAN,
DON'T THROW IT AWAY.

39:34.676 --> 39:36.678
ANDY, THIS ONLY
GONNA MAKE IT WORSE.

39:41.640 --> 39:42.728
PLEASE.

39:47.080 --> 39:48.255
OKAY.

39:48.386 --> 39:50.692
IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.

39:51.867 --> 39:52.999
IT'S OKAY.

39:54.783 --> 39:55.958
[MAN] HEY, GUYS,
HOLD IT RIGHT THERE.

39:57.351 --> 39:58.787
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN TO ME?

40:00.223 --> 40:01.573
YOU'RE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

40:06.969 --> 40:09.581
AND I'M WORKING
TOWER SEVEN AND YOU'RE AT SIX,

40:09.711 --> 40:11.278
-WE'LL BE TOGETHER.
-LOGAN.

40:12.453 --> 40:14.194
HERE'S THE LETTER YOU ASKED FOR.

40:15.587 --> 40:17.284
WHAT MADE YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND?

40:17.415 --> 40:19.329
HE'S A PERSON
OF EXCEPTIONAL SKILL.

40:19.852 --> 40:21.419
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT WE'D DO WITHOUT HIM.

40:22.855 --> 40:23.986
THANK YOU, LIEUTENANT.

40:24.117 --> 40:25.466
DON'T MENTION IT.

40:25.597 --> 40:29.078
LIEUTENANT,
THERE'S ONE MORE THING.

40:30.210 --> 40:32.517
SINCE IT LOOKS LIKE
I'LL BE AROUND FOR A WHILE,

40:33.431 --> 40:35.607
I WAS HOPING
WE COULD BECOME FRIENDS.

40:37.260 --> 40:38.697
DON'T PUSH YOUR LUCK.

40:42.178 --> 40:44.398
[GIGGLING]

40:47.619 --> 40:49.272
-HEY!
-HI.

40:49.403 --> 40:51.536
-NEED A LIFT?
-OH, NO THANKS.

40:51.666 --> 40:53.146
HAVE YOU SPOKEN WITH ANDY?

40:53.276 --> 40:56.366
YEAH, YEAH, HE GOT
A MEDICAL LEAVE OF ABSENCE

40:56.497 --> 40:58.978
FROM THE SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT.
HE'S GONNA UNDERGO

40:59.108 --> 41:01.459
INTENSIVE PSYCHOTHERAPY AND
HOPEFULLY THINGS WILL WORK OUT.

41:02.329 --> 41:03.330
HOPEFULLY.

41:04.070 --> 41:05.637
OH, I ALMOST FORGOT TO TELL YOU,

41:05.767 --> 41:07.073
THE POLICE FOUND YOUR TRUCK.

41:07.203 --> 41:08.553
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

41:08.683 --> 41:09.945
YEAH, THEY'RE HAVING IT
BROUGHT OVER.

41:10.859 --> 41:12.252
WELL, MAYBE I'LL GET LUCKY

41:12.382 --> 41:13.601
AND THERE WON'T BE
TOO MUCH DAMAGE.

41:23.568 --> 41:25.221
SO MUCH FOR GETTING LUCKY.

41:28.834 --> 41:31.663
HEY, HEY, HEY, THEY
DIDN'T TAKE THE SEAT BELTS.

41:32.359 --> 41:35.405
[LAUGHTING]

41:36.668 --> 41:40.668
[ENDING MUSIC]
